rpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Νώνιος Πι\n                    τέκτων\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Νώνιος\">Νώνιος\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Πι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Πι\">Πι̣\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τέκτων\">τέκτων\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"κάλλιστόν\">κάλ̣[λιστόν]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ποτε\">ποτε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῦτον\">τοῦτον\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἀνεῖ\n                    λε\">[ἀ]νεῖ-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>λε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"κίων\">κίων\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">καὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Μοῖρα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μοῖρα\">Μοῖρα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ὃς\">ὃς\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"κατέλειψε\">κατέλειψε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"πατρὶ\">πατρὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"λύπην\">λύπην\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"δεινοτάτην\">δεινοτάτην\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al8-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">8\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησε\">ἔζησε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτη\">ἔτη\u003C/span> κ̣β´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":243,"ptr":244,"ref":245,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"94 no. 2 fig. 2",{"target":134},{"_":136,"target":136},{"file":247,"uri":247,"title":248,"status":249,"editionAuthor":13,"type":251,"objectType":255,"material":256,"condition":257,"layoutDesc":259,"handNote":264,"date":412,"places":416,"geo":419,"provenance":62,"provenanceGeo":421,"country":76,"region":77,"settlement":424,"repository":425,"idno":428,"textLang":430,"tmNumber":432,"facsimile":433,"letterHeights":436,"publications":437,"zotero":440,"keywords":443,"html":449,"bibl":450},"ISic002945","A gymnasiarch crowns a group of youths",{"_":250},"edited",{"_":252,"ana":253,"ref":254},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},{"ana":258},"#condition.fragment",{"layout":260},{"p":261,"rs":262,"damage":263},"15 neatly carved lines of Greek letters, of which the first four are larger. There appears to be a slight vacat at the top; lines 1-3 are indented by the equivalent of 1-2 characters at most; from line 4 onwards the left indentation increases, with clear vacats after lines 5 and 6, and a fixed left margin (c.7 cm vacat) from line 7 onwards; a vacat is consistently inserted between each name in the list from line 7 onwards.",{"_":32,"ana":33,"ref":34},{"ana":36},{"lettering":265,"dimensions":393},[266,267],"Elegant letters with minimal serifs/terminations visible on longer strokes (e.g. on tau, sigma and epsilon). Alpha has straight bar; beta has smaller upper loop, with the two loops connected without meeting the vertical; epsilon has shorter middle bar; theta is a full-size circle with a detached horizontal stroke at the centre; kappa has full length arms; mu has near vertical first and last strokes, with the middle strokes meeting a small way above the baseline; xsi is formed of vertical with three horizontals, the middle one of shorter length; omicron is full-size; pi has equal length vertical strokes; sigma has horizontal topo and bottom strokes; phi 